  "description": "Change of use of part of the building from Town Hall (Sui Generis) to a 90 bed hotel (Use Class C1) with integral and ancillary uses including bar/restaurants, meeting rooms and conference/event space and change of use of the remainder of the building to a co-working space (Use Class E(g));  excavation of the basement; the provision of ancillary parking spaces, taxi drop off and service area with access from Harwood Road and Moore Park Road; erection of an additional storey at roof level (plus a storey of plant) and a four storey rear extension to the 1934 Extension following demolition of single storey corridor link to Harwood Road Wing; erection of additional storeys at second and third floor levels plus plant at fourth floor level to the Harwood Road Wing following demolition of former caretaker's flat at second floor level; erection of a fire escape stair and part three, part five storey (plus plant) extension to the rear of the Concert Hall/Council Chamber close to the Cedarne Road boundary; enclosure of central lightwell in connection with installation of new lifts; erection of new lift and stair cores to the north and south sides of the Harwood Road Wing; replacement of selected windows; various window alterations; installation of fixed glazed acoustic screens to exterior of selected windows and various other external alterations in connection with the change of use; and various internal demolition works and internal alterations including changes to the layout of the Council Chamber, the installation of fire lobbies, pod bathrooms, kitchenettes, lifts and the installation of secondary glazing to selected windows.\rPlease note: there is an associated Section 73 application related to these works: 2021/04043/VAR",
